# 1. Problem Statement

Current evaluation methods for AI agents are inadequate.

Most benchmarks (such as SWE-Bench) only evaluate the final outcome of an agent's task and ignore the intermediate reasoning process. Human evaluation is more reliable but is extremely expensive, slow, and difficult to scale.

The authors propose **Agent-as-a-Judge**, where one AI agent automatically evaluates another AI agent throughout the entire task-solving process.

