# 4. Limitations

- Focuses only on evaluation.
- Does not improve or repair failed AI agents.
- Does not introduce a self-reflection mechanism.
- Does not enable autonomous recovery after failures.
- Primarily validated on AI software development tasks.

---

# 5. How My Research is Different

This paper evaluates whether an AI coding agent performs correctly.

My research focuses on enabling an AI coding agent to recover after failure.

Instead of only judging the agent, my proposed Self-Reflection-Based Failure Recovery Framework allows the agent to:

- Detect failures
- Analyze why the failure occurred
- Generate reflective feedback
- Revise its reasoning
- Retry automatically
- Improve task completion without human intervention

Therefore, this paper provides an evaluation framework, while my dissertation proposes an autonomous recovery framework.

---

# Why This Paper is Useful

This paper is valuable because it:

- Shows the limitations of existing evaluation methods.
- Introduces DevAI, a realistic benchmark for AI coding agents.
- Demonstrates the importance of intermediate reasoning evaluation.
- Provides strong motivation for intelligent self-improving coding agents.

It supports my dissertation by showing that modern AI agents require richer feedback and better mechanisms for improving performance after failures.
